    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Genus of stocky, stilt-legged, Clydesdale-sized horse that lived in South America during the Ice Age Pleistocene epoch, between 2 million and 10,000 years ago. Hippidion possessed a highly distinctive, long, domed nasal bone. In an alternate classification, the stilt-legged build is seen as similar to the onager and kiang wild asses of Asia, thus suggesting they migrated from Asia across the Bering Strait.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
